  <h2>Database Migrations</h2>
  <pre><code>docker compose exec app alembic upgrade head</code></pre>
  <p>Migrations run automatically on first start. For upgrades, pull the latest image and restart.</p>

  <h2>Upgrading</h2>
  <pre><code>cd datanika-core
git pull origin master
docker compose up -d --build</code></pre>
  <p>The app container runs migrations automatically on startup.</p>

  <h2>Deploying on Kubernetes</h2>
  <p>A minimal Helm chart ships in-tree at <code>deploy/helm/datanika/</code>. It installs the same image as the Docker Compose path — one <code>app</code> Deployment (frontend + backend), one <code>celery</code> Deployment, bundled Postgres and Redis, and an optional ingress. Read the <a href="https://github.com/datanika-io/datanika-core/blob/master/deploy/helm/datanika/README.md">chart README</a> for the full <code>values.yaml</code> reference.</p>

  <p>Quickstart from a clone of <code>datanika-core</code>:</p>
  <pre><code>helm install my-datanika ./deploy/helm/datanika \
  --namespace datanika --create-namespace \
  --set secrets.POSTGRES_PASSWORD=$(openssl rand -base64 24) \
  --set secrets.REDIS_PASSWORD=$(openssl rand -base64 24) \
  --set secrets.SECRET_KEY=$(openssl rand -base64 32)

kubectl -n datanika get pods -w
kubectl -n datanika port-forward svc/my-datanika-app 3000:3000</code></pre>

  <div role="note" class="not-prose my-6 rounded-lg border border-amber-500/40 bg-amber-500/5 p-4 text-sm text-amber-100">
    <p class="font-semibold text-amber-300">⚠ Disable the bundled Postgres and Redis for real workloads</p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-amber-100/90">The chart ships single-replica <code class="bg-amber-500/10 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-amber-200">postgres</code> and <code class="bg-amber-500/10 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-amber-200">redis</code> Deployments so <code class="bg-amber-500/10 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-amber-200">helm install</code> works out of the box, but they are not production-grade: a single PVC, no replication, no backups. Point at managed databases instead:</p>
    <pre class="mt-3 bg-slate-900/70 border border-amber-500/20 rounded p-3 overflow-x-auto text-xs text-slate-200"><code>helm install my-datanika ./deploy/helm/datanika \
  --namespace datanika --create-namespace \
  --set postgres.enabled=false \
  --set externalDatabase.host=&lt;managed-postgres-host&gt; \
  --set env.POSTGRES_USER=&lt;user&gt; \
  --set env.POSTGRES_DB=&lt;db&gt; \
  --set secrets.POSTGRES_PASSWORD=&lt;password&gt; \
  --set redis.enabled=false \
  --set externalRedis.host=&lt;managed-redis-host&gt; \
  --set secrets.REDIS_PASSWORD=&lt;password&gt; \
  --set secrets.SECRET_KEY=$(openssl rand -base64 32)</code></pre>
    <p class="mt-3 text-amber-100/80">The chart wires <code class="bg-amber-500/10 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-amber-200">externalDatabase.host</code> into <code class="bg-amber-500/10 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-amber-200">DATABASE_URL</code> and <code class="bg-amber-500/10 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-amber-200">externalRedis.host</code> into <code class="bg-amber-500/10 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-amber-200">REDIS_URL</code> automatically.</p>
  </div>

  <p>Other things to know before you deploy to production:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>ReadWriteMany storage required.</strong> The <code>app</code> and <code>celery</code> pods share a <code>dbt_projects</code> PVC, so the chart requests an RWX storage class. On managed Kubernetes that usually means NFS, EFS, Azure Files, or Filestore; on bare metal, Longhorn or Rook/CephFS both work.</li>
    <li><strong>Migrations run on every app pod startup.</strong> <code>alembic upgrade head</code> executes before Reflex boots, which is fine at <code>app.replicaCount=1</code> but not yet safe for HA. A pre-install/pre-upgrade Hook Job is tracked separately.</li>
    <li><strong>Monitoring is not bundled.</strong> Unlike the Hetzner Docker Compose, the chart does not ship Grafana, Prometheus, or cAdvisor — run your cluster's existing observability stack and point it at the app's metrics endpoints.</li>
    <li><strong>Secret placeholders default to <code>CHANGE-ME</code>.</strong> The chart will install with them so <code>helm lint</code> passes, but always override <code>secrets.*</code> at install time.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Production Recommendations</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Reverse proxy</strong>: Use Nginx or Caddy in front for SSL termination</li>
    <li><strong>Backups</strong>: Schedule regular PostgreSQL backups (<code>pg_dump</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>Monitoring</strong>: Mount Grafana + Prometheus (docker-compose has optional profiles)</li>
    <li><strong>Security</strong>: Change all default passwords, restrict ports to localhost, use firewall</li>
    <li><strong>Resources</strong>: 8 GB RAM, 4 vCPUs recommended for production workloads</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What's Included</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>All 32 connectors (27 sources, 11 destinations)</li>
    <li>dbt transformations, pipeline builder, scheduling</li>
    <li>Multi-org with RBAC</li>
    <li>9 languages</li>
    <li>Everything in the Free plan — no artificial limits on self-hosted</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What's NOT Included (Cloud-only)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Paddle billing integration</li>
    <li>Managed infrastructure</li>
    <li>Automatic updates</li>
    <li>Priority support with SLA</li>
    <li>SSO (SAML/OIDC) — requires Enterprise plan on cloud, but SSO code is in the open-source core</li>
  </ul>

